organizer: NYC Boardgame Icebreakers - Meet ‚Ä¢ Drink ‚Ä¢  Play
event_date_time:
Wednesday, September 25, 2024
6:30 PM to 9:30 PM EDT
first_review: Will start off by saying the food was great and reasonably priced. We had a reservation and arrived but there was no host to seat us. Had to ask a bartender who brought us to our table. We asked to switch to a different empty table to get a better view of the game but was told by a guy sitting in the back on a laptop (manager? owner?) that those tables were reserved. I told him we had a reservation and he said no they are reserved for someone else. Of course, no one ended up showing up for those two tables and it appears they were reserved so the guy in the back could do his work without being bothered by having customers next to him. The two bartenders both waited on us and there was some confusion and frustration amongst them as to who was our waiter (that's for them to figure out, not us). Other than this, we really enjoyed, the food, drinks, and atmosphere. Not ready to give up on this place because it seems like a nice spot to watch the game and get some great food as well.

event_name: Startups and Business Networking Event NYC
event_date_time:
Wednesday, September 25, 2024
6:00 PM to 9:00 PM EDT
first_review:
The best board games bar in the city! We have tried quite a few of them all over Manhattan and Brooklyn, and E's has remained our absolute favorite. The vibe is always casual, friendly, and fun, and ramps up a bit on Friday and Saturday nights. They have a fantastic selection of games, enough that there is always a new one to try even though we have easily been there 20+ times over the last few years. The servers are always laid-back, there are different seating areas depending on the vibe you're looking for, and the burgers are AMAZING. The happy hour deals are also amazing, and incredible that it's most of the day! We have easily spent 5+ hours here on multiple occasions because you just don't want to leave.

We also recently hosted an event here, and it was such an easy and positive experience. Erin was so friendly and incredibly helpful with our options for how to book it, and really took the stress out of any part of the planning process. The day itself was perfectly smooth, and our guests really loved the relaxed and fun vibe of the bar - exactly what we hoped for. Hopefully we'll have a reason to book an event with E's again, but we will for sure be there regularly in the meantime!

first_review:
Bryant Park is truly one of the hidden gems in the city. It‚Äôs a beautiful and exceptionally clean park with so much to offer. Whether you‚Äôre looking to relax or get active, there‚Äôs something for everyone. I spent a lovely afternoon here and was really impressed by the variety of activities available. They have chess, ping pong, and even board games, making it a great spot to hang out with friends or spend some quiet time alone.

I also had lunch here, and the food options around the park are fantastic! From quick snacks to more filling meals, there‚Äôs no shortage of delicious choices. It‚Äôs the perfect spot to grab a bite while soaking in the lively atmosphere. Overall, I highly recommend checking out Bryant Park!

It‚Äôs an ideal place to unwind, enjoy some fun activities, and take in the beauty of the city.

event_date_time:

first_review: I took a lovely ballet drop in class here.  I did as the website suggested and downloaded the app beforehand.  When I arrived I was checked in quickly and headed up to the 3rd floor for locker rooms and a class in studio 1.  The locker room was very clean and neat.  There are day lockers for use.  You are able to bring your bag in the studio with you and set it on the windowsill durning class.  I took Dorit Koppel's ballet class which was AMAZING.  She's a wonderful teacher with great instruction and passion!   I am looking forward to the next time I am nearby and able to drop in for a class.  Their schedule is packed with classes so it's not hard to find something to work with your own schedule!
